A lawyer, Prince Williams-Joel, has unveiled three books on real estate to guide Nigerian and foreign investors in understanding sector. These are Understanding your rights as a tenant/landlord under the Nigerian law; Real Estate Investment: The due diligence guide; and Compilation of articles on law and property in Nigeria simplified. Williams-Joel said he was inspired to write the books because of the prospect in real estate. At the book launch, the author said: “Real estate investment is a booming sector. There are many Nigerians in the diaspora who want to venture into the business but need somebody to put them through.   ‘Change archaic curriculum to produce innovative graduates’     Firm achieves ISO accreditation     Why power should return to South, by CSOs   ‘’It is a specialised area for me where I have the experience, and I thought to use that knowledge to add value to this lucrative sector, and help Nigerians.” Williams-Joel hinted that his personal blog, which he has maintained since 2016, contains over 100 articles by him which will also help intending investors. “These publications will serve as sources of information to Nigerians who intend to venture into this sector. These books are real estate investment bible and a must-read for professionals and prospective investors.” The book reviewers – Henry Fomah and Imran Shitta-Bey – praised Williams-Joel for proffering solutions to problems in real estate. They encouraged Nigerians who want to venture into the real estate to get copies of the books.